items.title: How to Start & Market a Food Business from Your Home Kitchen

visible_instructors.name: Lisa
visible_instructors.title: Lisa Kivirist
visible_instructors.job_title: co-author HOMEMADE FOR SALE and Home Baker Crusader-Activist

items.headline: Work from home and launch your dream of running a successful homemade food product business from your kitchen.
objectives_summary: How to navigate your state’s cottage food laws that may allow you to sell non-hazardous baked goods or high-acid food products like jams, jellies or pickles, made in your home kitchen.

Understand what types of products are allowed to be produced and sold from a home kitchen, including diving into what “non-hazardous” means and the abundance of products you can potentially sell, from decorated cookies to pies, from cake pops to candies, from wedding cakes to dry mixes, as well as canned items like jams, jellies or pickles.

Based on your state’s cottage food law, understand where and how you can sell your product, along with how much revenue you can make. (Over half the states in the USA do not have any gross sales cap, so you can earn as much as you want, working from home!)
